## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="98d97-102">La definición de elemento de esquema XML denominada `xsi:choice` se utiliza para definir un elemento complejo que puede contener sólo un elemento secundario en una instancia (maxoccurs = 1).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-102">The XML schema element definition named `xsi:choice` is used to define a complex element that can contain only one child in an instance (maxoccurs = 1).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="98d97-103">Ese elemento secundario puede ser uno de los distintos tipos, y puede tener uno de los diversos nombres.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-103">That child can be one of several types, and it can have one of several names.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="98d97-104">Cada nombre está asociado con un tipo específico; Sin embargo, varios nombres pueden asociarse con el mismo tipo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-104">Each name is associated with a specific type; however, several names can be associated with the same type.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="98d97-105">Por este motivo, una instancia de ese tipo de elemento es imprecisa.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-105">Because of this, an instance of such an element is indistinct.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="98d97-106">Por ejemplo, considere el siguiente fragmento de esquema que define un elemento impreciso denominado `MyChoice`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-106">For example, consider the following schema fragment that defines such an indistinct element named `MyChoice`.</span></span>  
  
```  
<xsd:complexType name="MyChoice">  
 <xsd:sequence>  
 <xsd:choice minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1">  
 <xsd:element minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1" name="ChoiceOne" type="xsd:string" />  
 <xsd:element minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1" name="ChoiceTwo" type="xsd:string" />  
 </xsd:choice>  
 </xsd:sequence>  
</xsd:complexType>  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="98d97-107">El <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute> le permite asignar un valor de enumeración especial a cada instancia del miembro.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-107">The <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute> allows you to assign a special enumeration value to each instance of the member.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="98d97-108">Usted puede crear la enumeración o ésta puede ser generada por el [XML Schema Definition Tool (Xsd.exe)](~/docs/standard/serialization/xml-schema-definition-tool-xsd-exe.md).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-108">You must either create the enumeration yourself or it can be generated by the [XML Schema Definition Tool (Xsd.exe)](~/docs/standard/serialization/xml-schema-definition-tool-xsd-exe.md).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="98d97-109">La siguiente muestra de código de C# cómo <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute> se aplica a un `Item` campo; el <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute.MemberName%2A> propiedad identifica el campo que contiene la enumeración que se utiliza para detectar la elección.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-109">The following C# code shows how the <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute> is applied to an `Item` field; the <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute.MemberName%2A> property identifies the field that contains the enumeration that is further used to detect the choice.</span></span>  
  
```  
public class Choices{  
 [XmlChoiceIdentifier("ItemType")]  
 [XmlChoiceIdentifier("ChoiceOne")]  
 [XmlChoiceIdentifier("ChoiceTwo")]  
 public string MyChoice;  
  
 // Do not serialize this next field:  
 [XmlIgnore]  
 public ItemChoiceType ItemType;  
}  
// Do not include this enumeration in the XML schema.  
[XmlType(IncludeInSchema = false)]  
public enum ItemChoiceType{  
 ChoiceOne,  
 ChoiceTwo,  
}  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="98d97-110">Cuando este código está en su lugar, se puede serializar y deserializar esta clase estableciendo el `ItemType` campo en una enumeración adecuada.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-110">When this code is in place, you can serialize and deserialize this class by setting the `ItemType` field to an appropriate enumeration.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="98d97-111">Por ejemplo, para serializar el `Choice` (clase), el código de C# es similar al siguiente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-111">For example, to serialize the `Choice` class, the C# code resembles the following.</span></span>  
  
```  
Choices mc = new Choices();  
mc.MyChoice = "Item Choice One";  
mc.ItemType = ItemChoiceType.ChoiceOne;  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="98d97-112">Al deserializar, el código de C# es similar a lo siguiente:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-112">When deserializing, the C# code resembles the following:</span></span>  
  
```  
MyChoice mc = (MyChoice) myXmlSerializer.Deserialize(myReader);  
if(mc.ItemType == ItemChoiceType.ChoiceOne)  
 {  
     // Handle choice one.  
 }  
if(mc.ItemType == ItemChoiceType.ChoiceTwo)  
 {  
     // Handle choice two.  
 }  
if(mc.ItemType != null)  
 {  
     throw CreateUnknownTypeException(mc.Item);  
 }  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="98d97-113">Hay un segundo escenario cuando el <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute> se utiliza.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-113">There is a second scenario when the <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute> is used.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="98d97-114">En el esquema siguiente, el miembro es un campo que devuelve una matriz de elementos (maxOccurs = "unbounded").</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-114">In the following schema, the member is a field that returns an array of items (maxOccurs="unbounded").</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="98d97-115">La matriz puede contener objetos de la primera opción ("D-a-t-a") y de la segunda ("MoreData").</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-115">The array can contain objects of the first choice ("D-a-t-a"), and of the second choice ("MoreData").</span></span>  
  
```  
<xsd:complexType name="MyChoice">  
 <xsd:sequence>  
 <xsd:choice minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">  
 <xsd:element minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1" name="D-a-t-a" type="xsd:string" />  
 <xsd:element minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1" name="MoreData" type="xsd:string" />  
 </xsd:choice>  
 </xsd:sequence>  
</xsd:complexType>  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="98d97-116">La clase resultante, a continuación, usa un campo para devolver una matriz de elementos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-116">The resulting class then uses a field to return an array of items.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="98d97-117">Para cada elemento de la matriz, correspondiente `ItemChoiceType` también se debe encontrar la enumeración.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-117">For each item in the array, a corresponding `ItemChoiceType` enumeration must also be found.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="98d97-118">Las enumeraciones que coinciden se encuentran en la matriz devuelta por la `ItemsElementName` campo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-118">The matching enumerations are contained in the array returned by the `ItemsElementName` field.</span></span>  
  
```  
public class MyChoice {  
 [System.Xml.Serialization.XmlElementAttribute("D-a-t-a", typeof(string), IsNullable=false)]  
 [System.Xml.Serialization.XmlElementAttribute("MoreData", typeof(string), IsNullable=false)]  
 [System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute("ItemsElementName")]  
 public string[] Items;  
 [System.Xml.Serialization.XmlElementAttribute(IsNullable=false)]  
 [System.Xml.Serialization.XmlIgnoreAttribute()]  
 public ItemsChoiceType[] ItemsElementName;  
}  
[System.Xml.Serialization.XmlTypeAttribute(IncludeInSchema=false)]  
public enum ItemsChoiceType {  
 [System.Xml.Serialization.XmlEnumAttribute("D-a-t-a")]  
 Data,  
 MoreData,  
}  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="98d97-119">Al deserializar un objeto que incluye una variedad de opciones, utilice una estructura de control (como if... then... else estructura) para determinar cómo deserializar un valor determinado.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-119">When deserializing an object that includes a range of choices, use a control structure (such as an if...then...else structure) to determine how to deserialize a particular value.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="98d97-120">En la estructura de control, compruebe el valor de enumeración y deserializar el valor en consecuencia.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-120">In the control structure, check the enumeration value and deserialize the value accordingly.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="98d97-121">El siguiente ejemplo serializa una clase denominada `Choices` que incluye dos campos, `MyChoice` y `ManyChoices`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-121">The following example serializes a class named `Choices` that includes two fields, `MyChoice` and `ManyChoices`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="98d97-122">El <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute> se aplica a cada campo que especifica (a través de la <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute.MemberName%2A> propiedad) otro miembro de clase que obtiene o establece una enumeración que detecta el valor del miembro.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-122">The <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute> is applied to each field that specifies (through the <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute.MemberName%2A> property) another class member that gets or sets an enumeration that detects the member value.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="98d97-123">El `MyChoice` campo se puede establecer en un solo valor, con un miembro de enumeración correspondiente se encuentra en la `EnumType` campo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-123">The `MyChoice` field can be set to a single value, with a corresponding enumeration member found in the `EnumType` field.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="98d97-124">El `ManyChoices` campo devuelve una matriz de objetos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-124">The `ManyChoices` field returns an array of objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="98d97-125">El `ChoiceArray` campo devuelve una matriz de valores de enumeración.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-125">The `ChoiceArray` field returns an array of enumeration values.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="98d97-126">Para cada miembro de la matriz en la `ManyChoices` campo, un miembro correspondiente se encuentra en la matriz devuelta por la `ChoiceArray` campo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="98d97-126">For each array member in the `ManyChoices` field, a corresponding member is found in the array returned by the `ChoiceArray` field.</span></span>  
  
